  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.14.1\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nI have a template, that setup everything on one command\r\nIt run several process in parallele including one process to watch and compile contracts and other watching for artifact and deploying \r\n\r\nThe issue is that if someone use this template and have never used hardhat before, the 2 processes will ask the user the same question\r\n\r\nFurthermore, it is not that clear to the user why its process is waiting for.\r\n\r\nI tried to set in my template's config but it still ask the user the question\r\n\r\n```\r\nanalytics: {enabled: false},\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nThis assume you have zellij installed but you could follow the README instruction and run each process separately\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nrm ~/.config/hardhat-nodejs/telemetry-consent.json\r\nnpx degit wighawag/jolly-roger your-app-folder\r\ncd your-app-folder\r\n# edit contracts/hardhat.config.ts to add `analytics: {enabled: false},`\r\npnpm i\r\npnpm start\r\n```\r\n\r\nActually if you want to test without zellij, pnpm offer a parallel mode to execute multiple task and here the issue would be even worse, as there would be no way for the user to interact with the questions\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
